<subSubSection id="22A66546FFABFFE7FF11F9144A01F89A" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="6A0336CDFFABFFE7FF11F9144A01F89A" blockId="51.[151,1437,1753,2031]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">
<emphasis id="58C8EADFFFABFFE7FF11F9144A15F952" bold="true" box="[151,278,1753,1778]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">Etymology</emphasis>
. The genus name is derived from the ancient Greek Kairos, personification of opportunity, shown with one lock of hair on his forehead which reminds of the male ocular area modification of the 
<typeStatus id="B507886FFFABFFE7FB33F9334FE6F8B6" box="[1205,1253,1790,1814]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">type</typeStatus>
species; gender feminine.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="22A66546FFABFFE7FF41F8884E7CF84E" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="6A0336CDFFABFFE7FF41F8884F88F8FE" blockId="51.[151,1437,1753,2031]" box="[199,1163,1861,1886]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">
<emphasis id="58C8EADFFFABFFE7FF41F8884ACFF8FE" bold="true" box="[199,460,1861,1886]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">Diagnosis/Description</emphasis>
. See diagnosis and description of single known species below.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6A0336CDFFABFFE7FF41F8A44E7CF84E" blockId="51.[151,1437,1753,2031]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">
<emphasis id="58C8EADFFFABFFE7FF41F8A44A09F822" bold="true" box="[199,266,1897,1922]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">Notes</emphasis>
. The recent molecular phylogeny of 
<taxonomicName id="ADBC4D4EFFABFFE7FD21F8A448F5F822" authority="(Eberle et al. 2018)" authorityName="Eberle" authorityYear="2018" baseAuthorityName="Eberle" baseAuthorityYear="2018" box="[679,1014,1897,1922]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">
Pholcidae (
<bibRefCitation id="0E2D4B3CFFABFFE7FCA2F8A448EDF822" author="Eberle, J. &amp; Dimitrov, D. &amp; Valdez-Mondragon, A. &amp; Huber, B. A." box="[804,1006,1897,1922]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" pagination="141" refId="ref37668" refString="Eberle, J., Dimitrov, D., Valdez-Mondragon, A. &amp; Huber, B. A. (2018) Microhabitat change drives diversification in pholcid spiders. BMC Evolutionary Biology, 18, 141. https: // doi. org / 10.1186 / s 12862 - 018 - 1244 - 8" type="journal article" year="2018">
Eberle 
<emphasis id="58C8EADFFFABFFE7FCF3F8A648ADF822" box="[885,942,1897,1922]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">et al.</emphasis>
2018
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
placed 
<taxonomicName id="ADBC4D4EFFABFFE7FBCAF8A64FAAF822" authority="Huber &amp; Carvalho, 2019" authorityName="Huber &amp; Carvalho" authorityYear="2019" box="[1100,1193,1899,1922]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Kairona" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="51" pageNumber="70" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. n.">
<emphasis id="58C8EADFFFABFFE7FBCAF8A64FAAF822" box="[1100,1193,1899,1922]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">Kairona</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in a highly supported clade together with 
<taxonomicName id="ADBC4D4EFFABFFE7FE0BF8434907F805" authority="Huber &amp; Carvalho, 2019" authorityName="Huber &amp; Carvalho" authorityYear="2019" box="[397,516,1934,1957]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Saciperere" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="51" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. n.">
<emphasis id="58C8EADFFFABFFE7FE0BF8434907F805" box="[397,516,1934,1957]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">Saciperere</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(“Gen.n. Br15-45”); 
<taxonomicName id="ADBC4D4EFFABFFE7FC8AF8404F0DF806" authority="Huber, 2000" authorityName="Huber" authorityYear="2000" box="[780,1038,1933,1958]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Pisaboa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="58C8EADFFFABFFE7FC8AF840486BF806" box="[780,872,1933,1958]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">Pisaboa</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="0E2D4B3CFFABFFE7FCF1F8404F0DF806" author="Huber, B. A." box="[887,1038,1933,1958]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" pagination="1 - 348" refId="ref37855" refString="Huber, B. A. (2000) New World pholcid spiders (Araneae: Pholcidae): a revision at generic level. Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History, 254, 1 - 348. https: // doi. org / 10.1206 / 0003 - 0090 (2000) 254 &lt;0001: nwpsap&gt; 2.0. co; 2" type="journal article" year="2000">Huber, 2000</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
; and 
<taxonomicName id="ADBC4D4EFFABFFE7FBDFF8434E6BF806" authority="Huber, 2000" authorityName="Huber" authorityYear="2000" box="[1113,1384,1933,1958]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Waunana" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="58C8EADFFFABFFE7FBDFF8434FC1F805" box="[1113,1218,1934,1957]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">Waunana</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="0E2D4B3CFFABFFE7FB57F8404E6BF806" author="Huber, B. A." box="[1233,1384,1933,1958]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" pagination="1 - 348" refId="ref37855" refString="Huber, B. A. (2000) New World pholcid spiders (Araneae: Pholcidae): a revision at generic level. Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History, 254, 1 - 348. https: // doi. org / 10.1206 / 0003 - 0090 (2000) 254 &lt;0001: nwpsap&gt; 2.0. co; 2" type="journal article" year="2000">Huber, 2000</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. No morphological synapomorphy is known that joins these genera. They all share vertical hairs in high density on the male legs (femora and tibiae, or tibiae only) but this character is widespread among 
<taxonomicName id="ADBC4D4EFFABFFE7FBC3F8184E78F84E" authority="(Huber 2000)" authorityName="Huber" authorityYear="2000" baseAuthorityName="Huber" baseAuthorityYear="2000" box="[1093,1403,2005,2030]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Modisiminae">
Modisiminae (
<bibRefCitation id="0E2D4B3CFFABFFE7FB61F8184E70F84E" author="Huber, B. A." box="[1255,1395,2005,2030]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" pagination="1 - 348" refId="ref37855" refString="Huber, B. A. (2000) New World pholcid spiders (Araneae: Pholcidae): a revision at generic level. Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History, 254, 1 - 348. https: // doi. org / 10.1206 / 0003 - 0090 (2000) 254 &lt;0001: nwpsap&gt; 2.0. co; 2" type="journal article" year="2000">Huber 2000</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
